#Pre-requisits

* Ubuntu 10.04 machine

## Setting up an Ubuntu dev machine using Virtual Box

* Download VirtualBox - https://www.virtualbox.org/wiki/Downloads
* Install Ubuntu 10.04 LTS server edition (32 or 64bit) - https://help.ubuntu.com/community/Installation/MinimalCD
* Change the network mode to "Bridged adapter"
* Do not install any additional packages on Ubuntu; the wordpress-in-a-box scripts will do all this for you
* install SSH - sudo apt-get install ssh
  * mkdir ~/.ssh
  * vi ~/.authorized_keys  - then add your public key
  * chmod 600 .ssh/authorized_keys
  * chmod 700 .ssh
  * optional - configure your workstation's ~/.ssh/config to use the correct username & private key file

# Configuring your cluster controller machine
1. SSH into your Ubuntu machine
1. sudo apt-get update
1. sudo apt-get install git-core python-pip python-dev   (pip must be >1.0, check with pip --version)
1. sudo pip install littlechef paramiko
1. cd ~
1. git clone git://github.com/mrdavidlaing/wordpress-in-a-box.git

# Preparing a node
1. Edit your ~/.ssh/config so you can ssh <nodename> as root, or a sudoers user
1. from wordpress-in-a-box  -  fix node:<nodename> deploy_chef
1. from wordpress-in-a-box  -  fix node:<nodename> role:wordpress-in-a-box



